{"lemma":"حَلِيفٌ","slug":"حَلِيفٌ","root":"ح.ل.ف","root_slug":"ح-ل-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ل-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8853"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%81%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ally, confederate"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb حَلَفَ (ḥalafa)."},"ipa":["/ħa.liːf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8853","headword_ar":"حَلِيفٌ","root":"Hlf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilofN","text_ar":"حِلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whatever cleaves, clings, keeps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holds fast, to another thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haliyf","text_ar":"حَلِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":": whence one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Haliyfu Aljuwdi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ حَلِيفُ الجُودِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one cleaves to liberality"},{"kind":"text","text":"], &c. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Haliyfu Als~ahari","text_ar":"هُوَ حَلِيفُ السَّهَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is sleepless."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haliyfu All~isaAni","text_ar":"حَلِيفُ اللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharp-tongued;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Z, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent, in speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who conforms to the desire of his companion, as though he were a confederate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haliyfu Algarobi","text_ar":"حَلِيفُ الغَرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a poem of Sa'ideh Ibn-Ju-eiyeh, (Skr, K, * TA,) means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sharp spear-head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spear with a sharp head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Skr, TA:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly, horse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Skr, K.) Az says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sinaAnN HaliyfN","text_ar":"سِنَانٌ حَلِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sharp spear-head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and I think that it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hlyf","text_ar":"حليف"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the sharpness of its point is likened to the sharpness of the points of [the grass called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalofaA='","text_ar":"حَلْفَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Skr","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}